# Project Standards

## Tech Stack

- Vite + React + TypeScript for the frontend.
- Axios HTTP clients defined in `src/api/config.ts`.
- React Query for data fetching and caching.
- Tailwind CSS utilities plus custom utilities from `src/styles/utilities.css`.
- MUI (Material UI) components for typography and UI elements.

## TypeScript

- Avoid `any`. Prefer typed API responses from `src/api/types.ts` and explicit prop interfaces.
- Handle possibly `undefined` values defensively (nullish coalescing, default values, or early returns) rather than assuming presence.
- When adding new hooks (e.g. controllers), define small parameter/return interfaces instead of using raw objects.

## React Components

- Use **functional components** with named exports.
- Keep components "dumb" where possible; move data fetching and transformation into hooks/controllers (`*.controller.ts`) or API modules.
- For shared layout, use wrappers like `CardWrapper` instead of duplicating card markup across components.
- Prefer composition over deeply nested props; e.g. pass data into children instead of letting children fetch their own data when possible.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes for layout and spacing.
- Prefer project utilities from `src/styles/utilities.css` for theme colors (e.g. `bg-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `border-secondary`) instead of hardcoded color values.
- When mixing MUI + Tailwind, use MUI for semantic components (`Typography`, `Box`) and Tailwind for layout utilities (`flex`, `gap-*`, `p-*`, etc.).

## API & Error Handling

- Reuse `apiClient` and `authClient` from `src/api/config.ts` instead of creating new Axios instances.
- Add new API response shapes to `src/api/types.ts` and use them throughout the app.
- Use the existing interceptor + `triggerGlobalError` pattern for handling API errors, rather than ad-hoc `console.log`/`alert`.

## Environment Variables

- Use environment variables (e.g. `VITE_API_URL`, `VITE_OPENWEATHER_KEY`) for external endpoints and secrets.
- Never hardcode API keys or base URLs in components.

## Loading & UI States

- Prefer reusable components like `LoadingOverlay` for loading states.
- Prefer shared layout wrappers like `CardWrapper` instead of duplicating card markup across components.

